<1ST_LINE>r p PM-PoliticalQuotes     05-17 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Political Quotes,130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quotes From the Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments from the presidential
campaign trail:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   
   GEORGE BUSH, distancing himself on Monday from the Reagan
administration's environmental record: `I don't think we've been
doing enough to protect our environment in recent years. We need to
do more ... A new administration is a time for change, a time for
renewal. I will put the very best people we can find to work on our
environmental agenda.''
   
   PAT ROBERTSON, announcing his campaign is suspended: ``I suspend
my candidacy... but I do not now, nor will I ever suspend, my
advocacy of conservative and moral principles.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, saying neither Bush nor Michael Dukakis have
offered detailed plans to back up their promises: ``Let Mr. Bush
and Mr. Dukakis state their case. If they have a better plan, let
them come forward.''
