<HEAD>Reagan, Japanese Leader to Meet in London</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan will meet briefly in London
early next month with Japanese Prime Minister Noboru Takeshita
after the superpower summit in Moscow.
   White House deputy press secretary Roman Popadiuk acknowledged
Tuesday that the meeting would take place when Reagan stops in
London on his way back from his summit with Soviet leader Mikhail
S. Gorbachev. The meeting is expected to occur on June 3.
   Takeshita will be in London on a stopover before embarking on a
three-nation European trip that will take him to the Netherlands,
France and Belgium.
   In Janaury, Takeshita flew to Washington to hold talks with
Reagan, their first such meeting since the Japanese leader assumed
office last November.
