<1ST_LINE>r w AM-Lyng-Financial     05-17 0176</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Lyng-Financial,170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Agriculture Secretary Reports Outside Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Agriculture Secretary Richard E. Lyng reported
outside earnings of at least $119,500 last year, virtually
unchanged since he joined the Reagan cabinet in March 1986, his
financial disclosure report showed Tuesday.
   The outside earnings were in addition to his annual Cabinet
salary, which was raised to $99,500 in February 1987.
   According to the statement, Lyng owns assets worth at least
$775,000, primarily in real estate investments and a family seed
business in Modesto, Calif. His 1987 outside income was in the
range of $119,500 to $260,000.
   Lyng's liabilities, secured by mortgages and home equity, are at
least $300,000, according to the report.
   Income, assets and liabilities are reported only in broad ranges
by the financial disclosure reports.
   When Lyng underwent Senate confirmation proceedings in March
1986, he reported 1985 assets of at least $775,000 and an income in
the range of $205,000 to $344,000. The 1985 income included $82,500
salary from his private consulting firm, which he sold after being
chosen for the USDA post.
</TEXT>
