<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--KoreaMeet     05-17 0147</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Korea Meet,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>U.S.-South Korean Defense Meeting June 7-9</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United States and South Korea will hold
their 20th annual Security Consultative Meeting in Seoul from June
7 to June 9, the Pentagon said Tuesday.
   The U.S. delegation will be led by Defense Secretary Frank C.
Carlucci, who intends to tour various American and South Korean
units in the field during his visit.
   The sessions will be hosted by South Korean Minister of National
Defense Oh Ja Bok and the two men intend to ``carefully review ...
plans for security cooperation by the two nations to help ensure
the success of the Seoul Olympics,'' the Pentagon said in a
statement.
   The Security Consultative Meetings rotate each year between
Seoul and Washington, and focus on issues surrounding the
stationing of American troops in South Korea and the military
threat posed by neighboring North Korea.
</TEXT>
