<HEAD>EDITORS:</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Election officials in as many as 21 of Oregon's 36 counties will
release an ``early pickup'' of returns from Tuesday's Democratic
and Republican presidential primaries shortly after the polls close
at 11 p.m. EDT.
   In many of the 21 counties, this initial report will include
returns from most or all precincts, giving the appearance in vote
summaries transmited by AP that the county is complete, or nearly
so.
   In reality, the ``early pickup'' from about 550 of the state's
2,338 precincts will represent between 10 percent and 80 percent of
the anticipated vote, depending on the county.
   We will attempt to keep you advised of the portion of the
expected vote contained in these summaries as the evening
progresses.
   The AP
