   Here is a geographical breakdown of the March
trade balance, based on figures released Tuesday by the Commerce
Department. All numbers are negatives, reflecting trade deficits.
   ``Up'' connotes a worsening, or widening, of the deficit.
``Down'' connotes an improvement, or narrowing of the deficit.
   Total trade deficit: $9.75 billion, down from $13.83 billion in
February.
   Canada: $1.14 billion, down from $1.46 billion in February.
   Western Europe: $911 million, down from $1.56 billion.
   Japan: $4.55 billion; up from $4.53 billion.
   Newly industrialized countries of Asia (Singapore, Hong Kong,
Taiwan and South Korea): $1.39 billion; down from $2.90 billion.
   Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC): $686
million; down from $1.3 billion.
   Mexico: $348 million, down from $645 million.
  
