<2ND_LINE>AM-Philippines-Fire,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Major Manila Department Store Suffers Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire broke out at a major suburban
Manila department store and burned out of control until Wednesday
morning, almost 12 hours later, fire officials said. Three people,
including two firefighters, were injured.
   The blaze broke out about 9:30 p.m. (9:30 a.m. EDT) Tuesday on
the second floor of the Shoemart Department store in a shopping
center in Makati and quickly spread to three of the building's four
stories, officials said.
   They said the fire was brought under control about 9 a.m.
Wednesday. The store was closed when the fire began. Besides the
two injured firefighters, a store employee suffered smoke
inhalation.
   There was no immediate estimate of damage.
   The store is in the Makati Commercial Center, which includes two
luxury hotels _ the Manila Garden and the Intercontinental. The
hotels were not threatened and no guests were evacuated.
