   So-called corporate ``deadbeats'' _ companiesout how it crashed at
the bottom of a steep hill,
killing three people and injuring 20.
   ``We have some new information about a possible cause,'' state
police Sgt. Dennis Cody said. He declined to elaborate.
   Cody said police plan to talk with the driver again this
afternoon. He said investigators will try to determine whether
mechanical failures or high speed contributed to Monday afternoon's
accident.
