<HEAD>Baxter Travenol becomes Baxter International on Wednesday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shareholders of Baxter Travenol Laboratories Inc.
voted Tuesday to change the company's name to Baxter International
Inc., effective Wednesday.
   The vote at the annual shareholders meeting was part of a
continuing campaign to project a more unified image of the company
and its products, Baxter said in a statement.
   ``The proposal to change the name of our company is much more
than cosmetic,'' Vernon R. Loucks Jr., Baxter's chairman and chief
executive, told shareholders. ``It represents the very core of our
strategy.''
   Baxter acquired American Hospital Supply Corp. in 1985, and
Loucks said officials have worked over the past two years to
integrate the two companies.
   Baxter, based in the Chicago surburb of Deerfield, is a leading
international producer of health-care products, systems and
services. It had 1987 revenue of $6.2 billion.
