<HEAD>Depressed Actress Commits Suicide After Stock Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BROADSTAIRS, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An actress depressed over the loss
of her savings in last fall's stock market crash drowned herself
off the east coast of England, an inquest ruled Tuesday.
   Coroner Rebecca Cobb recorded a suicide verdict in the case of
Robin Ross, who used the stage name Wendy Ross and had appeared on
U.S. television shows including ``Dallas'' and ``Charlie's Angels.''
   Miss Ross' mother, Virginia, testified her 33-year-old daughter
had come back to Britain and changed completely after losing her
money. She reportedly lost 100,000 pounds, the equivalent of
$186,000.
   Mrs. Ross said her daughter, who lived in Canada at the time of
the October crash, kept telling her mother she felt poor.
   A doctor also testified that Miss Ross had visited him in
January and was ``extremely anxious and depressed.''
   On April 11, Miss Ross told her mother she was going on a
shopping errand, drove to a beach near Broadstairs, swam out to sea
and drowned.
</TEXT>
