<HEAD>Sugarman Negotiating Sale of Cement Company</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Burt Sugarman, the Hollywood
producer and investor seeking to buy Media General Corp., is
negotiating the sale of his cement and resource recovery companies.
   Sugarman's Giant Group Ltd. announced Monday it was discussing
the sale with Environmental Treatment & Technologies Co. of
Findlay, Ohio, for $110 million cash plus warrants to buy up to 1
million shares of Environmental Treatment stock at $15 a share.
   Sugarman last week boosted his offer for Media General to $70 a
share from $61.50 a share, which amounts to $1.78 billion for the
shares he doesn't already own in the Richmond, Va., newspaper and
broadcasting company.
   Sugarman has declined to comment on how he would finance the
offer, which has been spurned by Media General management.
   The Giant Group sale talks include Keystone Cement Co. in Bath,
Pa., and Giant Cement Co. in Harleyville, S.C., which together
produce more than 1.5 million a year and are powered by burning of
hazardous waste.
   Giant's other major investments include 24.4 percent of the
television game show company Barris Industries Inc. and 23 percent
of Rally's Inc., a fast food chain.
   Giant and Barris combined hold 10.1 percent of Media General.
