<1ST_LINE>r f AM-May-Closings     05-17 0130</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-May-Closings,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>May Closing Cincinnati Ayres Stores</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   May Department Stores Co. said Tuesday it will
close and sell its three remaining Cincinnati-area L.S. Ayres
department stores by June 15 because the chain is trailing
competitors in the market.
   Two months ago, May announced it was closing the chain's
downtown Cincinnati store.
   ``Ayres did not have a competitive position in the Cincinnati
market. McAlpin's, Lazarus and Sears are the leaders and we're, at
best, fourth in the area,'' said James Abrams, a May spokesman.
   Abrams said the company has received inquiries about the stores,
but he declined to say who might be a prospective buyer.
   The 14 Ayres stores in Indiana would not be affected by the
closings, Abrams said. The Ayres division is based in Indianapolis.
</TEXT>
