<1ST_LINE>u f AM-OilPrices     05-17 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Oil Prices,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Oil Prices Mixed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oil futures prices closed mixed after a session
of apathetic trading Tuesday.
   Contracts for June delivery of West Texas Intermediate, the
benchmark U.S. crude, advanced 10 cents to settle at $17.76 per
42-gallon barrel on the New York Mercantile Exchange.
   Among June contracts for refined products, wholesale prices for
unleaded gasoline rose 0.01 cent to 52.74 cents per gallon, while
heating oil moved 0.20 cent lower to 47.78 cents per gallon.
   Analysts said the market was sleepy, with no news having any
lasting impact on trading during the day.
   Despite widespread expectations of stronger second-half demand,
many traders have been reluctant to take strong positions in the
market until the course of the next meeting of the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries becomes clear, they said.
   The meeting begins June 8 in Vienna, Austria.
</TEXT>
