<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Bell&Howell     05-17 0165</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Bell & Howell,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Shareholders Approve Bell & Howell Buyout</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EVANSTON, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bell & Howell Co. shareholders on Tuesday
approved a $702 million buyout led by Texas financier Robert M.
Bass and members of Bell & Howell's management.
   Shareholder approval cleared the way for completion of the
buyout of the Skokie-based information-services company by Robert
M. Bass Group Inc., Acadia Partners L.P. of Fort Worth, Texas, and
certain Bell & Howell executives including Gerald E. Schultz,
chairman and chief executive officer.
   The group will pay each stockholder $64 per share for their
common and preferred stock, Bell & Howell said in a statement.
   Financing arrangements for the deal were consummated shortly
after the shareholder approval, the company said.
   Financing includes $200 in senior subordinated debt, of which
Acadia Partners is buying $30 million; $344 million in bank
financing; $100 million equity participation in the form of cash
and Bell & Howell stock; and $58 million of Bell & Howell's cash on
hand.
</TEXT>
